label: beef round
definition: A beef cut that comes from the 'round', the rear leg of the beef.
comment: Sometimes referred to as the “Beef Hip.”

label: beef round (raw)
definition: A beef round cut that is raw.

label: beef bottom round
definition: A beef cut that comes from the outside of the rear leg.
comment: Given the name “Bottom” because anatomically it is located below the Top Round and the Eye of Round in the Round primal.

definition: A meat cut from the beef bottom round that is raw.

label: beef chuck
definition: A beef cut that extends from the neck to the fifth rib and includes the shoulder blade and upper arm.

label: beef chuck (raw)
definition: A meat cut from beef chuck that is raw.

label: beef chuck tender
definition: A beef cut that consists of M. supraspinatus which lies dorsal to the medial ridge of the blade bone.
comment: The name comes from its shape which is long and narrow with a pointed tip, similar to a Tenderloin.

label: beef chuck tender (raw)
definition: A meat cut from beef chuck tender that is raw.

label: beef chuck tender steak

label: beef chuck roll
definition: A large, boneless cut that comes from between the ribs and backbone. It contains a mix of tender and somewhat tough muscles, which are fabricated into smaller cuts known as the chuck eye roll and the chuck under blade.
comment: Extension of the Ribeye Roll that remains in the Chuck.

label: beef chuck roll (raw)
definition: A meat cut from beef chuck roll that is raw.

label: beef chuck eye roll

comment: The top portion of the Chuck Roll that most resembles a Ribeye Roll.

Equivalence axiom: 'beef chuck eye roll' and 'has quality' some 'raw'
definition: A meat cut from the beef chuck eye roll that is raw.

label: beef under blade

label: beef sierra steak

label: beef sierra steak (raw)
definition: A beef sierra steak that is raw.

label: beef denver steak

label: beef shoulder clod
definition: A large muscle system which lies dorsal and posterior to the elbow joint, ventral and posterior to the ridge of the scapula (blade bone) and is anterior to the 6th rib.
comment: Centred around the scapula or blade bone in the Chuck. Scapula is removed to make this a boneless subprimal.

label: beef shoulder clod (raw)

label: beef shoulder clod arm roast

comment: Commonly referred to as clod heart. Leave whole or cut into roasts, but remove large connective tissue to assist with tenderness.

comment: However, internal connective tissue should be removed to preserve that tenderness.

label: beef loin
definition: A beef primal cut that comes from the area below the backbone .
comment: The area below the backbone is home to some of the most tender and popular cuts of beef, such as the Tenderloin, Strip Steak, T-Bone and Porterhouse Steaks. Loin cuts are exceptionally prepared on the grill or under a broiler.

Exact Synonym: beef loin porterhouse steak bone in

label: beef T-bone steak
